caption: Chinese American here. Waitress demanded that the tip will be 10% minimum. As a customer I tip what I want and last time I checked, you earn your tip. She didn't do anything. The best waiter there is the short Chinese guy who always greets you in English too or Chinese. I can speak fluent Cantonese. Sometimes waitress and waiters rely on tips and bring their China ways here which are very aggressive to ask for tips just like when they haggle with prices in China or drag foreigners to their stores to scam you. To all that eat here, if you want to tip ZERO due to poor service, you can. Do not feel threatened by the waitress to tip. I hope the manager sees this. The next time my girlfriend wants to eat here, I will complain to the manager. I would give 0/5 rating if I can. Food is overpriced here anyway from a Chinese person's perspective.

We were served with amazing hospitality by one of the service staff; not sure if he was the maitre'd or manager, but he offered to seat us with all smiles. The prices were decent and the food was good. However, after we had paid, and I tipped as much as I could afford, the waitress literally scoffed at it and asked for more. I added a little more, which was already stretching my budget, and she took it but arrogantly remarked that it should have been more. I did not get her name, but she was so rude that it ended the entire meal on a very sour note. Yes, I wish I could tip more, but tips are not supposed to be mandatory, and her asking for money just proved she did not deserve her tips.

Lee Wing Wah is a fantastic restaurant if you're looking for some authentic Chinese/Hong Kong family style food. They also have your nontraditional dishes (orange chicken, sweet and sour pork, etc.) if that's what you're into. My family has been coming here for 15+ years to celebrate birthdays, graduations, or if we don't feel like cooking that night. I don't know why people are complaining about the service in the reviews because the service is fast and straight to the point. If you need something, just ask.. That's just how Chinese restaurants operate, fast and straightforward and that's how most restaurants are going to be like in Chinatown so get over it. We love visiting Chinatown and we make it an adventure by using the Chicago Water Taxi to arrive. It always feels like we are on vacation. One of the problems we have is that we have found our favorite places in Chinatown, so we don't really venture out and try new places.  We were looking for desert, after dinner. We tried a bakery a few doors down from here and the cake was not very good. So we decided we needed a fresh watermelon drink to wash it down.  We walked up to check out the menu and a lady immediately opened a window and asked what we wanted. It was great and efficient. We did not even have to walk into the restaurant. We decided to grab a fresh watermelon smoothie. The lady went behind the bar and started making our drink.  We waited outside and our smoothie arrived very quickly. There is even a nice little shelf installed on the outside edge of the window. The prices were also great too. It was only $3 plus tax per smoothie. A few doors down there was another location and they were charging $4.45 plus tax per smoothie. That location was crowded. I wonder if these people knew they could save money a few doors down at this place.  The watermelon smoothie was really good. In fact, I don't think I've ever had a bad watermelon smoothie anywhere. It is always refreshing and delicious. So I am happy to say we have a new stop added on to our Chinatown visits. Plus you can't beat the price of the smoothies too.  Now it looks like this restaurant has a full menu. I can not comment on the food or what the experience is inside the restaurant. We only used the walk up window to grab a fresh fruit smoothie and that was a great experience.  I'm glad we now have a new stop now.

I am Chinese and this is my family's favorite restaurant in Chinatown. Very authentic, tasty, generous portions of food for reasonable prices. Very extensive menu. The atmosphere is very authentic, too. I always bring visiting friends and family here and I have never been disappointed with anything I've ever ordered. Their lunch specials are an incredible deal, too - a full dish with an eggroll for like $5. You can't beat that! I've been known to go there for the lunch special, and then order two or three of the lunch special items to bring home for later.
